  '<p>Every encrypted blob starts with a four-byte header that identifies the algorithms used. This is what makes algorithm agility possible: any component can be swapped without rewriting existing data, because <code>b.crypto.decrypt()</code> dispatches on the header bytes, not on a guess at the active default.</p>',
