  '<h2 id="vault">Vault</h2>',
  '<p>The vault holds the operator\'s master keypair. Every sealed column, signed audit row, and webhook signature traces back to a key that lives here. Two modes: <em>plaintext</em> (the keypair sits on disk in clear; useful for development and a demo, never for production) and <em>wrapped</em> (the private key is encrypted under a passphrase-derived key — Argon2id stretches the passphrase to a wrapping key; the encrypted key file is what lives on disk). The wrapped path is the default. Operators supply the passphrase via <code>BLAMEJS_VAULT_PASSPHRASE</code>; the framework refuses to boot in wrapped mode without it. Plaintext-mode boots print a warning on every start: <code>WARNING: PLAINTEXT mode — vault.key is unprotected on disk</code>.</p>',

  '<h3>b.vault.seal(plaintext) / b.vault.unseal(sealed) <a class="anchor" href="#vault-seal">#</a></h3>',
